Remind yourself of this, be overwhelmed with the gospel.

18:51.611 --> 18:57.618
And when you are saturated with the gospel, what you're gonna discover is that you are more apt

18:57.730 --> 19:01.754
to share the message of the gospel with those who are around you.

19:02.375 --> 19:03.276
And here's what Paul says.

19:03.356 --> 19:06.779
He wants the church accord to be overwhelmed with the gospel.

19:06.819 --> 19:08.441
So he gives them this statement.

19:08.461 --> 19:16.949
Saint Corinthians 521, he made him who knew no sin to be sinned on our behalf so that we might become the righteousness of God in him.

19:17.009 --> 19:19.132
Now, are y'all listening to say yes?

19:19.652 --> 19:20.813
Because I want you to grab ahold of this.

19:20.853 --> 19:21.914
Are y'all paying attention to say yes?

19:22.575 --> 19:23.076
Here it is.

19:23.756 --> 19:25.458
On the cross at Calvary.

19:25.986 --> 19:27.989
through his sacrificial death.

19:28.971 --> 19:36.963
Jesus had imputed into his spiritual bank account, your sin and my sin.

19:38.685 --> 19:43.092
God made him who knew no sin to be sin.

19:44.294 --> 19:45.115
Why did he do this?

19:46.096 --> 19:51.725
So that he could bear in his body the wrath and judgment that you deserve that I deserve.

19:52.686 --> 19:55.090
That Jesus died in our place.

19:55.490 --> 19:56.852
for our sin.

19:57.693 --> 19:58.574
But here's the great news.

19:59.275 --> 20:01.819
When you come to faith in Jesus Christ, you know what happens?

20:02.260 --> 20:09.911
What happens is that God actually imputes into your spiritual bank account the perfect righteousness of Jesus.

20:11.493 --> 20:12.274
Isn't that phenomenal?

20:12.474 --> 20:13.456
Say, well, that doesn't make sense.

20:13.756 --> 20:19.024
How could God put perfect righteousness into a sinners bank account?

20:19.425 --> 20:20.686
That seems absurd.

20:20.746 --> 20:23.250
How much more absurd does it seem?

20:23.618 --> 20:28.064
that God would take your sin and place it on a perfectly righteous man.

20:29.045 --> 20:29.726
And yet he did it.

20:31.188 --> 20:34.392
And he did all of this so that he might bring us into a relationship with him.

20:35.113 --> 20:40.300
He did all of this so that you and I might know him forever.

20:41.341 --> 20:42.462
You've got to be overwhelmed with that.

20:43.323 --> 20:44.345
I've got to be overwhelmed with that.

20:44.365 --> 20:51.474
I've got to remind myself of this and I've got to be willing to share the message of the gospel even when I'm scared to death to do it.

20:52.962 --> 20:58.108
So what I want to do very quickly, I've been doing this over the past several months and maybe you haven't picked up on it.

20:58.128 --> 20:59.410
I've been doing it subliminally.

21:01.172 --> 21:05.217
But I've actually been teaching you how to share the gospel by using four simple words.

21:05.777 --> 21:07.580
So I'm going to give them to you very straight now, right?

21:07.600 --> 21:08.741
So here are the four simple words.

21:08.781 --> 21:16.811
If you'll jot them down, you can write them in the flat leaf of your Bible and these statements that go with these simple words, it's going to help you when you go and share the gospel scared.

21:16.831 --> 21:19.474
The first word is the word accident.

21:19.586 --> 21:20.127
accident.

21:20.187 --> 21:20.747
Here's the statement.

21:21.048 --> 21:23.170
You are not an accident.

21:23.851 --> 21:24.792
You were created by God.

21:24.812 --> 21:25.853
You were created for God.

21:27.315 --> 21:27.976
How simple is that?

21:28.576 --> 21:32.241
There is no person on the planet who is an accident.

21:33.322 --> 21:36.846
Every single person, every single person created by God and for God.

21:37.166 --> 21:37.867
So you're not an accident.

21:38.027 --> 21:39.809
Here's the second word and that's the word abandoned.

21:40.550 --> 21:41.011
Abandoned.

21:41.311 --> 21:42.232
And here's the fact, right?

21:42.512 --> 21:44.655
We have abandoned God.

21:45.135 --> 21:45.936
Now, how have we done that?

21:45.956 --> 21:47.378
We've done that through our sin.

21:47.714 --> 21:50.098
We've all sinned and fallen short of God's perfect standard.

21:50.318 --> 21:52.621
And the wages of our sin is death.

21:53.122 --> 21:55.566
And there is nothing that we can do to get rid of our sin.

21:55.626 --> 21:56.487
We can't be good enough.

21:56.507 --> 21:57.508
We can't be religious enough.

21:57.749 --> 22:00.873
We cannot do anything to wash away our sin.

22:01.034 --> 22:04.098
We are separated from Him.

22:04.138 --> 22:08.064
And while we cannot get to Him, here's the phenomenal news.

22:08.104 --> 22:09.887
And that's the third word, approached.

22:11.369 --> 22:12.411
And here's what happened.

22:12.451 --> 22:17.458
While we couldn't get to God, the Bible teaches us that God approached us in Jesus.

22:17.890 --> 22:18.371
Did he not?

22:19.271 --> 22:21.374
Jesus came born of a virgin to ensure his purity.

22:21.614 --> 22:23.956
He lived a sinless life on your behalf and on my behalf.

22:24.297 --> 22:28.161
And then on the cross at Calvary, he died of death that you deserve and I deserve.

22:28.381 --> 22:31.024
He was buried and then he was gloriously resurrected.

22:32.826 --> 22:33.867
He approached us.

22:34.628 --> 22:40.394
He came to us because we could not get to him, which leads me to the fourth word, and that is accept.

22:40.414 --> 22:41.415
And this is a calling here.

22:41.895 --> 22:44.498
We must accept him by faith.

22:44.994 --> 22:48.059
We've got a turn from our sin place, our trust in the Lord Jesus Christ.

22:48.299 --> 23:02.159
And if you'll have those four words in your heart and in your mind, when you are in a conversation with someone who does not know the Lord, those four words can become lynch pens for the conversation so that you're sharing with another person.

23:02.600 --> 23:10.171
Listen, you're not an accident, but we've all abandoned God, but God has approached us in Jesus and we must accept Him by faith.

23:11.453 --> 23:13.496
What a simple message.

23:13.516 --> 23:14.738
And we've got to learn how to do it.

23:15.234 --> 23:16.515
even when our heart is racing.

23:17.877 --> 23:25.866
We gotta be faithful to do it because one day we're gonna stand before Jesus and give an account to whether or not we were faithful to it.

23:26.847 --> 23:27.868
So what's my prayer for you?

23:27.908 --> 23:28.429
Very simple.

23:28.529 --> 23:29.810
Live thinking of the end.

23:30.631 --> 23:32.293
Live speaking on behalf of heaven.

23:32.693 --> 23:35.156
And then I would say live overwhelmed with the gospel.

23:36.017 --> 23:38.199
So I wanna pray those into our lives now, let's bow.

23:38.219 --> 23:44.146
Father, in the name of Jesus, help us to be faithful to this great call upon our lives

23:44.834 --> 23:56.031
this call to share the message of Jesus Christ, to make disciples, to serve using our spiritual gifts, help us to never abandon that call, but help us to be faithful.

23:56.051 --> 24:00.358
Lord, I pray for Concord and for this awesome church family.

24:00.398 --> 24:05.746
Lord, I ask in the name of Christ that you would help every single one of them to live thinking of the end.

24:05.806 --> 24:13.458
And when they would they stand before you, Lord, I pray they stand before you with great joy in their hearts, not ashamed of their Christian life.

24:14.370 --> 24:16.813
but knowing full well that they have sought to be faithful.

24:18.095 --> 24:24.404
Lord, I pray as well that they would live speaking on behalf of heaven as ambassadors for the sake of the kingdom.

24:24.905 --> 24:26.948
Doing it even while they are scared.

24:28.149 --> 24:34.719
Lord, would you also grant them grace to be overwhelmed with the gospel?

24:37.322 --> 24:42.930
We'll give you glory for how you work in each life and how you use us for your purposes.

24:46.242 --> 24:48.965
And with your heads bowed, your eyes closed, nobody's looking this morning.

24:49.826 --> 24:55.373
But you say, Levi, listen, all of this that you've preached this morning, I've never given my life to Jesus.

24:56.034 --> 24:58.137
I've never genuinely trusted in Him.

25:00.199 --> 25:02.862
Can I encourage you right where you are if you need to give your life to Christ?

25:02.882 --> 25:04.705
You can pray something very simple.

25:06.086 --> 25:09.751
And speaking to the Lord, the Bible says, whoever calls on the name of the Lord shall be saved.

25:10.111 --> 25:11.613
You might be a guest here this morning.

25:11.633 --> 25:12.695
You might be from out of town.

25:12.995 --> 25:15.538
You might be a long time church goer.

25:15.938 --> 25:19.763
but you know that you've never genuinely trusted Jesus.

25:19.783 --> 25:24.208
You can't point back to a time when you remember giving your life to Christ.

25:25.150 --> 25:30.857
Let me encourage you, right now, today can become that day, the day you gave your heart to Jesus.

25:31.778 --> 25:35.382
So let me encourage you, you can pray in your seat silently.

25:35.443 --> 25:38.206
Just as I pray aloud, just trying to help you just pray something like this.

25:38.266 --> 25:44.594
Just say, Lord, today I admit to you that I'm a sinner, that I cannot save myself.

25:46.530 --> 25:48.753
But I believe Jesus died for me and was resurrected.

25:49.855 --> 25:55.042
And the best way that I know how I'm turning from my sin and putting my trust in you.

25:55.062 --> 25:56.765
Help me live unashamed of who you are.

25:59.168 --> 26:00.149
And help me to walk with you.

26:02.693 --> 26:04.075
With your head bowed, your eyes closed.

26:04.095 --> 26:07.840
Nobody's looking around this morning, but you say, Levi, just pray with you and gave my life to Christ.

26:08.361 --> 26:09.062
Here's what I want you to know.

26:09.082 --> 26:10.945
The first step of obedience is baptism.

26:11.365 --> 26:12.747
We don't do that because we're Baptists.

26:12.767 --> 26:14.770
We do that because the Bible tells us to do it.

26:15.714 --> 26:18.597
It should be baptized as a new believer in Jesus.

26:18.657 --> 26:20.659
You go public with your faith.

26:22.241 --> 26:23.703
You saw that this morning already.

26:24.223 --> 26:26.766
We'd love to set up a time for you to be baptized in the days ahead.

26:26.786 --> 26:32.973
So in a moment, when we stand to our feet, if you've given your heart to Christ, I'm going to invite you to leave the place where you've been seated throughout this hour.

26:33.033 --> 26:34.354
Just come forward.

26:34.374 --> 26:35.876
I'll be here in the front of others as well.

26:35.916 --> 26:36.917
We want to pray for you.

26:37.297 --> 26:39.600
We want to help you along in your walk with Jesus Christ.

26:40.040 --> 26:41.842
We want to set up a time for you to be baptized.

26:44.258 --> 26:46.180
The last hour we had someone come forward.

26:48.463 --> 26:49.945
And I'd love to celebrate with you today.

26:49.985 --> 26:54.151
Or maybe you feel that this is where God wants your family.

26:55.512 --> 26:57.835
Or you as an individual to be a member.

26:57.895 --> 26:59.357
You want to join Concord?

26:59.397 --> 27:02.281
You want to partner with this place to make disciples everywhere?

27:02.641 --> 27:08.048
So if God's calling your family to join or you as an individual to join, I want to invite you to come as well this morning.

27:08.449 --> 27:09.850
Had a family come last hour.

27:09.930 --> 27:12.754
We'd love to celebrate with you as we did with them.

27:13.346 --> 27:15.234
So Lord, as always, we give you the invitation.

27:16.037 --> 27:17.162
We trust that you'll work in it.

27:17.544 --> 27:19.372
And that's in the name of Jesus Christ that we pray.

27:19.914 --> 27:20.215
Amen.

27:20.255 --> 27:20.878
Let's stand to our feet.

27:20.898 --> 27:23.730
And while we sing, you come this morning if God's calling you today.

